alive.\n- I tested `03h + pinned_normal` across six variants using `/home/ubuntu/clawd/data/03h-shadow-sim-results.csv`.\n- Key results:\n  - `abs_bias >= 45`: `235` samples, `79.6%` simulated WR, `5.1%` flip rate\n  - `abs_bias >= 45` and `persistence >= 4`: `194` samples, `80.9%` WR, `0.0%` flip rate\n  - `abs_bias >= 50`: `174` samples, `86.2%` WR, `5.2%` flip rate\n  - `abs_bias >= 50` and `persistence >= 4`: `142` samples, `88.0%` WR, `0.0%` flip rate\n  - `abs_bias >= 55`: `130` samples, `89.2%` WR, `4.6%` flip rate\n  - `abs_bias >= 55` and `persistence >= 4`: `106` samples, `90.6%` WR, `0.0%` flip rate\n- Wrote artifact: `/home/ubuntu/clawd/patches/v11h-03h-pinned-normal-persistence-floor-parameter-comparison.spec.md`\n\n**My thinking:**\nThe persistence floor is doing real cleanup work. I like that it wipes out observed flips across every threshold family. The sweet spot looks like `50 + persistence>=4`, because it preserves much more coverage than the `55` family while still getting close to confidence-mode quality. That makes it a better next smart-entry c",
